article.headline: High Point 109, VMI 92
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 32 points and pulled down 25 rebounds to propel High Point to a 109-92 Big South Conference win Saturday night over VMI. VMI's loss came despite 32 points from Reggie Williams, whose performance couldn't carry the Keydets (12-18, 5-9 Big South) over the Panthers (21-9, 11-3). High Point overcame a slim Keydet lead at 16:42 in the first half with a 24-7 scoring run. High Point led 51-42 at halftime and VMI never got closer than 62-59 before the Panthers pushed their lead into double digits and hitting 10 of 11 from the free throw line in the final minutes. Eugene Harris and Mike Jefferson each scored 20 points for the Panthers and Landon Quick and Melvin Crowder had 10 each. VMI had scoring help from Chavis Holmes, who hit four 3-pointers and had 21 points for the game. Matt Murrer had 17 points and nine rebounds and Travis Holmes added 15 points. High Point converted the Keydets' 16 turnovers into 18 points.
